bio.experienceSummary: I have extensive experience in the child care field, providing a loving, caring, and nurturing environment for children of all ages, from infants through early teens. Adaptable to special needs children and their care. I'm also a pet lover.

description.displayText: As a single parent, I couldn't have raised such a great son without her.   She was always there to support both my son and me.  She has great values and I trusted every decision she made when my son was in her care.  He is now 23 and both he and I still keep in touch with Cathi and see her regularly.  I would hire her in a heartbeat.....

bio.experienceSummary: I am a mother of 2. I have had guardianship of 2 other children and fostered 3 brothers. My kids are 13 and 15 now but I've had custody of other children since I'm 22. I babysat (for free) all of my family and friends children so they can work since new Born and I have an 11 month old niece that I get for 1 week a month since she's 3 months old. I just have a deep love for children. Seeing and making children happy fills my heart and it my joy in life

Hello! I am a 27-year-old middle school language arts teacher living in Woodbridge, NJ. I AM FULLY COVID-19 VACCINATED!! I have my bachelor's degree in English and my Master's in Teaching with certifications in k-6, special ed., and middle school (5-8) language arts. Personally, I have worked with children for as long as I can remember with jobs such as babysitting, assistant preschool teacher, arts & craft specialist at my local summer camp, and my recent teaching experience. I have experience with children ages newborn through 8th grade as well as children with special needs. I can also provide you with references if needed!

**I am a full time teacher during the year and am not looking for reoccurring weekday jobs**

description.displayText: Melissa was our summer babysitter for our two boys (elementary school age) for two summers (2019 and 2020).  Melissa truly loves children; she took the boys to the library, the park, to get ice cream after camp.  Melissa became part of our family and she will always be. My boys adore her.  We wish that she lived closer so she can babysit for us again this summer.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as fun, easy going and cheerful

I like working with kids because I love children. Love seeing their development growth and if I can have a piece of enhancing and empowering them to be great individuals then of course it's a pleasure. 

One thing you should know about me is your child is your precious jewel and my job is to keep that jewel save and treat it just as special as is.
I provide safety, care and fun to a child as I babysit. Ensuring they feel safe, comfortable to be themselves while having a wonderful time. Every child is different so I learn who they are, their personality, their likes and dislike. I am flexible and open to assisting in anyways I can. I love arts and craft, I'll play sport, I'll go on outings such as museum, park anywhere they want to go I'm willing to travel. Babysitting is not just a job but a passion.

description.originalText: Kiaora is a delightful and creative sitter who our five-year-old daughter immediately loved. We absolutely trust her to take great care of her.

bio.experienceSummary:
Currently teacher aide at a Learning Center (special need stage school)
Also provide child care services at a Center with kids who are receiving therapy
Have babysat off this website for the past 7 years off and on
majority of experience with special needs and multiple disabilities from mild-profound disabilities 
Familiar with wheelchair needs, feeding, and changing for all ages.

I grew up in a big family both immediate and extended. I am the oldest of seven and I have been surrounded by babies/young children my entire life. I also babysit at school. I have been with that family for almost two years now and continue to have a good relationship with them. I am trustworthy, responsible, and reliable.

description.displayText: Kayleigh has been our babysitter for the past 4 years.  My kids love it when she watches them because she is fun, plays games with them and has even taken them out to dinner. We have had such a great experience with Kayleigh. She is reliable and responsible and a great role model. We are lucky to have her and your family would be too.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello my name is Talia. I am CPR certified. I have been working with children of all ages for the last 6 years. I speak Spanish.

Hi! I'm Claudia and I'm 24 years old. I have 6+ years of paid experience, I've taken care of kids from newborn to 14 years old. I'm very patient and loving, I'm comfortable with taking care of pets, meal prep, and dropping off and picking up from activities. I love play time and I'm good with arts and crafts. I did community service as an assistant in an after-school program for middle schoolers so I have a lot of experience helping out with homework and school projects. I worked at a Daycare school for 3 years as a Pre-K assistant teacher and eventually became a Preschool lead teacher. I have a driver's license with a clean record and my own car. I'm First Aid/AED/CPR certified for Adult and Pediatrics. I speak Spanish fluently. I'm fully vaccinated against Covid 19. I would be happy to help in anything I could!

description.displayText: I've hired Claudia to babysit my boys on two occasions. She is the best and my kids love her! Always arrives early and willing to stay late. She's very patient with the kids and friendly. No complaints at all!

bio.experienceSummary: Thank you for checking out my profile! I was a Social Studies teacher in the Dominican Republic for a few years. I've had my NJ Child Care License for 2 years now. I am highly qualified, motivated, fun, high alert, and am detail-oriented. :) Please note that my primary language is Spanish, I do understand English and speak it to some extend. I am new to care. com but most definitely not new to child care. I have raised 3 beautiful intelligent children of my own, which I am more than proud of. Please feel free to message me if you have any questions or would like to schedule a online or over the phone meeting/interview.

Hello families!

Please feel free to message me with any questions or concerns - more than happy to discuss further!
